snippet.title: Johnny Depp 'launches fresh multi-million dollar court case' against Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp is reported to be preparing to face Amber Heard in court again in a new 'multi-million dollar court case'.


It comes a month after the ex spouses faced off in a bitter high court battle that is expected to reach verdict next week.


According to the Mail On Sunday, Depp's lawyers are expected to serve papers in America that could result in his ex wife Amber giving evidence again about their turbulent marriage.

Amber, 34, previously claimed that the Hollywood actor was abusive and violent towards her during their three years together.

Father-of-two Johnny, 47, has strongly denied the allegations and took The Sun's publishers News Group Newspapers to court in July over an article that called him a 'wife beater.'

As well as his case against NGN, Johnny is also taking action against Amber in the US State of Virginia over a column she wrote in the Washington Post in 2018.

While the Aquaman actress did not give any names in the article, she described herself as 'a public figure representing domestic abuse.'

Following the rumours another court hearing could be on the cards, a source close to Amber told the Mail: "It seems that [Johnny] will stop at nothing to ruin her".
